query_preview:
ConfigWatch incorrectly adds trailing slashes to all context paths when watching Consul config changes. This breaks FILES format because it treats files as folders, causing HTTP 404 errors from Consul. The issue emerged in release 1.1 where response code checking was added, previously ignoring 404s by accident. The fix requires checking the config format and avoiding trailing slashes for FILES mode. ConfigWatch spring.cloud.consul.config.format if (format == FILES) {
    // Don't add trailing slash
} else {
    // Add trailing slash for FOLDERS format
}

